main event: A security guard observed an unidentified flying object (UFO) over the Naval Air Station, Key West, Florida on September 6, 1968.
interesting points: The object was described as bright white in color, triangular in shape, and approximately 50-75 feet in diameter.
The object was observed hovering at an estimated altitude of 3000-4000 feet above the airfield for approximately 15 minutes.
The object suddenly accelerated and departed the area at a high rate of speed, estimated to be in excess of 1500 mph.
The sighting was reported to the UFO Reporting Center, and the incident is being investigated by the Foreign Technology Division, United States Air Force.
A photograph was taken of an unidentified object over the Everglades near Miami, Florida on September 9, 1968, but the analysis was inconclusive and the case was closed.
sighted object: a bright white, triangular-shaped object in the sky
